<div class="mb-requirement-container">
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-14092">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> </span>
      <b>NOTE: </b> The official merit badge pamphlets are now free and
      downloadable
      <a
        href="https://filestore.scouting.org/filestore/Merit_Badge_ReqandRes/Pamphlets/Entrepreneurship.pdf"
        target="_blank"
        >HERE</a
      >
      or can be purchased at the
      <a href="https://www.scoutshop.org/" target="_blank ">Scout Shop.</a>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-4575">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 1. </span>
      In your own words, define entrepreneurship. Explain to your counselor how
      entrepreneurs impact the U.S. economy. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
      <a href="https://youtu.be/KEuTpRkZqiY" target="_blank"
        >Why Entrepreneurs Are Important for the Economy (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a
        href="https://www.investopedia.com/articles/personal-finance/101414/why-entrepreneurs-are-important-economy.asp"
        target="_blank"
        >Why Entrepreneurship Is Important to the Economy (website)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-4576">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 2. </span>
      Explain to your counselor why having good skills in the following areas
      are important for an entrepreneur: communication, planning, organization,
      problem solving, decision making, basic math, adaptability, technical and
      social skills, teamwork, and leadership. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
      <a href="https://youtu.be/iAWeIBUjRqQ" target="_blank"
        >The Key Skills of Successful Entrepreneurs (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/JiGJttyiqFs" target="_blank"
        >The Entrepreneurial Mindset: From Kids to Entrepreneur (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a
        href="https://online.hbs.edu/blog/post/entrepreneurial-skills"
        target="_blank"
        >6 Skills All Entrepreneurs Need (website)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-4569">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 3. </span>
      Identify and interview an individual who has started a business. Learn
      about this person's educational background, early work experiences, where
      the idea for the business came from, and what was involved in starting the
      business. Find out how the entrepreneur raised the capital (money) to
      start the business, examples of successes and challenges faced, and how
      the business is currently doing (if applicable). Discuss with your
      counselor what you have learned.
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-4577">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 4. </span>
      Think of as many ideas for a business as you can, and write them down.
      From your list, select three ideas you believe represent the best
      opportunities. Choose one of these and explain to your counselor why you
      selected it and why you feel it can be successful. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
      <a href="https://youtu.be/qJp0j4g3k3o" target="_blank"
        >Business Ideas: Finding Your Niche (video)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-4564">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 5. </span>
      Create a written business plan for your idea that includes all of the
      following: <br /><i>Resources:</i>
      <a href="https://youtu.be/8iDv_WzL3GI" target="_blank"
        >How To Write a Business Plan With 6 Easy Simple Steps (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/7ykkhepT9aE" target="_blank"
        >Writing a Business Plan (video)</a
      >
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-4564 mb-requirement-id-4584">
        (a)
        <b>Product or Service</b>
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-4584 mb-requirement-id-4585">
        (1) Describe the product or service to be offered.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-4584 mb-requirement-id-4586">
        (2) Identify goals for your business. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/9DE5gBCNizA" target="_blank"
          >How To Set SMART Goals for Your Business (Guide) (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/yA53yhiOe04" target="_blank"
          >Achieve More by Setting Smart Goals (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-4584 mb-requirement-id-4587">
        (3) Explain how you can make enough of the product or perform the
        service to meet your goals.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-4584 mb-requirement-id-4588">
        (4) Identify and describe the potential liability risks for your product
        or service. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/vlDj76cGzZY" target="_blank"
          >Mitigating Risk &amp; Managing Liabilities (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-4584 mb-requirement-id-4589">
        (5) Determine what type of license, if any, you might need in order to
        sell or make your product or service. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/1pjqjy1VYwI" target="_blank"
          >What Is Licensing (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/evjpbwHWYLg" target="_blank"
          >How To License your Business Idea Step-by-Step (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-4564 mb-requirement-id-4590">
        (b)
        <b>Market Analysis</b>
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-4590 mb-requirement-id-4591">
        (1) Identify the types of people who would buy your product or service.
        <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/g37DCEKILno" target="_blank"
          >How To Define Target Market and Customers in Business Plan (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-4590 mb-requirement-id-4592">
        (2) Identify your business's competitors, and describe their strengths
        and weaknesses. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/c6UUOXnbNkA" target="_blank"
          >What Is a Competitive Analysis? (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/yhtGs4cjJ8Q" target="_blank"
          >Advantages to Competitors (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-4590 mb-requirement-id-4593">
        (3) Describe what makes your product or service unique. <br /><i
          >Resources:</i
        >
        <a href="https://youtu.be/wpT4OYwSw04" target="_blank"
          >Unique Selling Proposition (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/OEDKuuhipKw" target="_blank"
          >3 Strategies to Find Your Unique Selling Proposition (USP) (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-4564 mb-requirement-id-4594">
        (c)
        <b>Financial</b>
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-4594 mb-requirement-id-4595">
        (1) Determine how much money you will need to start your business, and
        identify how you will obtain the money. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/Oqw1Rj0MVJo?si=r-FuxHY-H6p28B0c"
          target="_blank"
          >How To Build Financial Projections for Your Startup (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/pACo_F_O4Cc?si=xBCevTWHtYYP9_R6"
          target="_blank"
          >How To Calculate Startup Costs (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-4594 mb-requirement-id-4596">
        (2) Determine the cost of offering your product or service and the price
        you will charge in order to make a profit. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/xQWUm_eHjGk" target="_blank"
          >PRICING STRATEGY: How To Find The Ideal Price For A Product
          (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-4594 mb-requirement-id-4597">
        (3) Describe what will happen with the money you make from the sales of
        your product or service. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/kmOj1usAmKM" target="_blank"
          >Revenue vs Gross Income/Profit/Earnings vs Net Income/Profit/Earnings
          (Bottom Line) (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-4564 mb-requirement-id-4598">
        (d) <b>Personnel </b> <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://www.liveplan.com/blog/planning/5-steps-to-creating-an-investor-ready-personnel-plan"
          target="_blank"
          >How To Create an Investor-Ready Personnel Plan and Forecast Employee
          Costs (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-4598 mb-requirement-id-4599">
        (1) Determine what parts of the business you will handle yourself, and
        describe your qualifications.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-4598 mb-requirement-id-4600">
        (2) Determine whether you will need additional help to operate your
        business. If you will need help, describe the responsibilities and
        qualifications needed for the personnel who will fill each role.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-4564 mb-requirement-id-4601">
        (e) <b>Promotion and Marketing</b> <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/auRTKgS1bTM" target="_blank"
          >How To Develop an Effective Marketing Strategy (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-4601 mb-requirement-id-4602">
        (1) Describe the methods you will use to promote your business to
        potential customers. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/QusJ4fpWQwA" target="_blank"
          >What Is Marketing in 3 Minutes | Marketing for Beginners (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/Mw8mvlKAjeA" target="_blank"
          >Tips for Elevator Pitches (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-4601 mb-requirement-id-4603">
        (2) Explain how you will utilize the internet and social media to
        increase awareness of your product or service. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/h14XHhCbYdo" target="_blank"
          >Four Steps To Building Brand Awareness Through Social Media
          (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-4601 mb-requirement-id-4604">
        (3) Design a promotional flyer or poster for your product or service.
        <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/KglO4C412DA" target="_blank"
          >Canva Tutorial For Beginners | How To Design A Flyer in Canva
          (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/DWiM3GLw0Z8" target="_blank"
          >Canva Brochure Design Tutorial (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/7eeUsOQI5EA" target="_blank"
          >How To Make a FLYER in Google Docs (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/pPYcPlTFbwU" target="_blank"
          >How To Use Lucidpress to Make a Pamphlet or Brochure (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-4583">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 6. </span>
      When you believe your business idea is feasible, imagine your business
      idea is now up and running. What successes and problems might you
      experience? How would you overcome any failures? Discuss with your
      counselor any ethical questions you might face and how you would deal with
      them. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
      <a href="https://startup.info/challenges-startups-face/" target="_blank"
        >15 Challenges Startups Face (and How To Overcome Them) (website)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/HbrpYeobu-Q" target="_blank"
        >Understanding Business Ethics (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/QNB9hnRfgdk" target="_blank"
        >Failures Are Lessons for Future Success (video)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
